er%20President%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20poll%2C%20which%20surveyed%201%2C150%20US%20adults%20nationwide%2C%20including%20975%20registered%20voters%2C%20showed%20Trump%20with%20significant%20advantages%20over%20Harris%20on%20several%20of%20the%20issues%20voters%20consider%20most%20pressing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20which%20of%20the%20two%20candidates%20had%20a%20better%20approach%20to%20the%20economy%2C%20unemployment%20and%20jobs%2C%20voters%20in%20the%20poll%20picked%20Trump%2047%25%20to%2037%25.%20Trump%20has%20had%20an%20edge%20on%20the%20economy%20throughout%20the%20campaign%20and%2026%25%20of%20voters%20in%20the%20latest%20poll%20cited%20jobs%20and%20the%20economy%20as%20the%20country's%20most%20pressing%20problem%2C%20compared%20to%2024%25%20who%20cited%20political%20extremism%20and%2018%25%20who%20pointed%20to%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20biggest%20edge%20in%20terms%20of%20policy%20could%20be%20on%20immigration%20issues%2C%20where%20he%20has%20put%20forward%20hardline%20proposals%20that%20include%20mass%20deportations%20of%20migrants%20in%20the%20country%20illegally.%20Some%2048%25%20of%20voters%20in%20the%20latest%20poll%20said%20Trump's%20approach%20to%20immigration%20was%20best%2C%20higher%20than%20the%2033%25%20who%20picked%20Harris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20poll%20also%20showed%20Harris'%20advantage%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20political%20extremism%20to%20be%20dwindling.%20Some%2040%25%20of%20voters%20in%20the%20poll%20said%20she%20had%20a%20better%20approach%20to%20handling%20political%20extremism%20and%20threats%20to%20democracy%2C%20compared%20to%2038%25%20who%20picked%20Trump.%20Harris'%20two-point%20lead%20on%20the%20issue%20compared%20to%20her%20seven-point%20lead%20over%20Trump%20on%20extremism%20the%20Oct%2016-21%20poll.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20has%20emphasized%20Trump's%20role%20in%20the%20Jan%206%2C%202021%20assault%20on%20the%20U.S.%20Capitol%20by%20his%20supporters%2C%20who%20aimed%20to%20ove