over%20Allred%20(50%25%20to%2046%25)%20among%20likely%20voters%2C%20but%20in%20the%20same%20poll%2C%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20led%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20by%20ten%20points%20(52%25%20to%2042%25).%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.fivethirtyeight.com%2Fpolls%2Fsenate%2F2024%2Ftexas%2Fgeneral%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eother%20polls%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20race%2C%20including%20ones%20from%20Marist%20College%2C%20Morning%20Consult%2C%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Houston%20Hobby%20School%20of%20Public%20Affairs%2C%20all%20showed%20Cruz%20with%20single-digit%20leads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20competitiveness%20of%20the%20race%20led%20the%20Senate%20Majority%20PAC%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Democratic%20political%20action%20committee%20tied%20to%20Senate%20Majority%20Leader%20Chuck%20Schumer%20of%20New%20York%20%E2%80%94%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Ftexas-senate-allred-cruz-ad-campaign-abortion-69b5a7db65cd82d1bbe258d874ae6c6c%23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epour%20%245%20million%20into%20the%20contest%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20days%2C%20as%20the%20Texas%20race%20is%20now%20widely%20viewed%20as%20the%20party's%20best%20opportunity%20to%20flip%20a%20red%20seat%20this%20year.%20In%20total%2C%20Allred%20has%20raised%20more%20than%20%2480%20million%20for%20the%20Senate%20race%2C%20according%20to%20his%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20key%20fact%20remains%3A%20Allred%20will%20have%20to%20overcome%20the%20state's%20Republican%20lean%20in%20order%20to%20oust%20Cruz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6679d62-bcb0-468d-971d-22ac5da907f8%5C%22%3EReproductive%20rights%20and%20the%20economy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sat%20down%20with%20Allred%20before%20a%20recent%20block%20walk%20kickoff%20event%20in%20Houston%2C%20where%20the%20former%20NFL%20player%20and%20civil%20rights%20attorney%20laid%20out%20his%20case%20against%20Cruz's%20reelection%20bid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20something%20significant%20stuck%20out%20during%20our%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20red-state%20Democrats%20often%20shied%20away%20from%20speaking%20out%20too%20forcefully%20regarding%20reproductive%20rights.%20However%2C%20after%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%20was%20overturned%20by%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20along%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-abortion-maternal-health-desert-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas'%20strict%20abortion%20ban%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Allred%20lambasted%20%26quot%3Bextremism%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20argued%20would%20seriously%20affect%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Times%2FSiena%20poll%2C%20likely%20voters%20in%20Texas%20ranked%20the%20economy%20as%20their%20top%20issue%2C%20with%2027%25%20of%20respondents%20expressing%20this%20opinion.%20(The%20second-and-%20third%20ranked%20issues%20were%20immigration%20and%20abortion%2C%20with%2015%25%20support%20for%20each%20issue.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20individual%20stories%20of%20people%20denied%20miscarriage%20care%20or%20denied%20care%20when%20pregnancies%20weren't%20viable%20and%20having%20to%20leave%20the%20state%20are%20horrific%2C%26quot%3B%20Allred%20told%20me%20after%20he%20spoke%20at%20a%20reproductive%20rights-focused%20rally%20headlined%20by%20Harris%2C%20which%20also%20featured%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharris-beyonce-abortion-reproductive-rights-trump-allred-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20appearance%20by%20Beyonc%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20many%20of%20these%20women%20that%20have%20come%20forward.%20It's%20personal.%20It's%20also%20impacting%20every%20other%20aspect%20of%20Texas%20life%2C%20from%20our%20medical%20schools%20to%20our%20universities%20to%20our%20business%20climate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d605ce1a-811a-4765-b109-fcf121e7d70a%5C%22%3EThe%20electoral%20map%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20then-Rep.%20Beto%20O'Rourke%20traversed%20Texas%20during%20his%20Senate%20campaign%20and%20in%20the%20process%20visited%20all%20of%20the%20state's%20254%20counties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Cruz%20eventually%20won%2C%20he%20bested%20O'Rourke%20by%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-senate-race-results-ted-cruz-defeats-beto-orourke-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2.6%20percentage%20points%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20by%20roughly%20215%2C000%20votes%20out%20of%20more%20than%208.3%20million%20ballots%20cast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226868%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sen.%20Ted%20Cruz%20of%20Texas%20speaks%20at%20a%20campaign%20rally.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6720e818a0a0cc14f2248bab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224579%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECruz%20was%20first%20elected%20to%20the%20Senate%20in%202012.%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Bell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EO'Rourke's%20campaign%20that%20year%20worked%20to%20energize%20Democratic%20voters%20%E2%80%94%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20young%20and%20progressive%20voters%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20town%20hall%20events%20became%20a%20signature%20part%20of%20his%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllred's%20campaign%20approach%20is%20a%20bit%20different%20than%20the%20one%20pursued%20by%20O'Rourke%2C%20who%20represented%20the%20El%20Paso%20area%20in%20Congress%20from%202013%20until%202019.%20He's%20seeking%20to%20maximize%20Democratic%20turnout%20as%20well%2C%20but%20he's%20conducted%20serious%20outreach%20to%20independents%20and%20Republicans%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20his%20moderate-minded%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20record%20of%20being%20the%20most%20bipartisan%20Texan%20in%20Congress%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%20during%20our%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20sort%20of%20ethos%20that%20Allred%20takes%20with%20him%20on%20the%20campaign%20trail%20across%20Texas%2C%20a%20behemoth%20of%20a%20state%20that%20contains%20huge%20cities%20and%20scores%20of%20medium-sized%20and%20smaller%20cities%20and%20towns%20in%20between.%20It%20can%20take%20around%20thirteen%20hours%20to%20drive%20across%20Texas%20from%20the%20east%20to%20the%20west.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20massive%20state%2C%20and%20what%20happens%20in%20one%20part%20of%20the%20state%20is%20not%20always%20known%20in%20the%20other%20part%20of%20the%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20Allred%20told%20me%2C%20adding%20of%20his%20experience%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20come%20across%20any%20Texans%20who%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20handout%2C%20but%20I%20come%20across%20Texans%20who%20are%20looking%20for%20somebody%20who's%20going%20to%20be%20on%20their%20side.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20in%20Texas%20already%20perform%20strongly%20in%20cities%20like%20Austin%2C%20Dallas%2C%20Houston%2C%20and%20San%20Antonio.%20But%20in%20the%20Trump%20era%2C%20Democrats%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-haley-suburbs-gop-problem-north-carolina-virginia-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20won%20over%20more%20suburban%20voters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20phenomenon%20that%20has%20helped%20the%20party%20immensely%20in%20other%20Sun%20Belt%20states%20like%20Arizona%20and%20Georgia.%20And%20if%20Allred%20is%20to%20defeat%20Cruz%2C%20he'll%20have%20to%20put%20up%20extremely%20strong%20numbers%20with%20suburban%20voters%20across%20the%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20P.%20Jones%2C%20a%20political%20science%20professor%20at%20Rice%20University%2C%20told%20me%20in%20a%20interview%20that%20Cruz%20is%20in%20a%20tougher%20spot%20compared%20to%20other%20Texas%20Republicans%20because%20he%20lacks%20substantial%20%26quot%3Bcrossover%26quot%3B%20support.%20Republicans%20for%20decades%20have%20flexed%20their%20political%20muscle%20in%20the%20state%20based%20on%20their%20strong%20support%20from%20the%20party%20faithful%20and%20conservative-leaning%20independents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Cruz%2C%20a%20onetime%20GOP%20presidential%20candidate%2C%20has%20cut%20a%20polarizing%20profile%20both%20in%20Texas%20and%20on%20the%20national%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20doesn't%20have%20much%20appeal%20to%20the%20sort%20of%20soft%20Republicans%2C%20independents%2C%20and%20moderate-to-conservative%20Democrats%20in%20the%20same%20way%20that%20Gov.%20Greg%20Abbott%20or%20Sen.%20John%20Cornyn%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it's%20not%20a%20large%20amount%2C%20but%20he%20starts%20off%20at%20a%20disadvantage%20in%20that%20he%20needs%20to%20pretty%20much%20win%20all%20of%20the%20Republican%20vote%20and%20make%20sure%20that%20Republicans%20turn%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb1e4296-476c-4197-8a8c-71b3d735e2a4%5C%22%3ECruz%20'too%20small'%20for%20Texas%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20campaign%20trail%2C%20Allred%20has%20targeted%20Cruz's%20infamous%202021%20trip%20to%20Canc%C3%BAn%2C%20Mexico%2C%20which%20occurred%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fted-cruz-cancun-trip-houston-police-security-detail-winter-storm-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20Texans%20were%20without%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20a%20severe%20winter%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20our%20conversation%2C%20Allred%20depicted%20Cruz%20as%20someone%20who%20doesn't%20have%20a%20broader%20vision%20for%20one%20of%20the%20fastest-growing%20states%20in%20the%20country%2C%20which%20now%20boasts%20over%2030%20million%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Cruz%20campaign%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTexas%20is%20incredibly%20diverse%20and%20dynamic%2C%20but%20we%20have%20been%20governed%20by%20extremists%20who%20I%20think%20have%20put%20at%20risk%20all%20of%20the%20positives%20about%20our%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20Allred%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BTed%20Cruz%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20someone%20who%20I%